QuestList: ELLL 4, The thing that is closest to my heart is my teddy bear Pinker. He is a small and pale pink cutie. I know he is not something rare like a limited edition labubu doll or whatever those haunted things are called, but he is very special to me and I don't even know why. He is my Woody (Toy Story reference). My granny bought him for me for my 4th birthday and I didn't realize his speciality until one random day when I was 6 or 7. I don't know what happened, I just felt this unexplainable form of love towards him which I hadn't felt before which was why I named him after my most favorite cartoon then "Pink Panther". I used to host birthday parties for him with Britania cake and I would invite all my friends for it and of course it goes without saying that they can't come empty handed ! It's the same relationship Andy has with Woody in Toy Story , Woody is just special without any specific reason and although Andy couldn't spend time with him as he grew old he still loved him the same. Although I know Pinker is made of just fluff and cloth I can't help but view him as a friend. Maybe I see him as a representation of my childhood, the carefree days I spent outside without worrying about safety or creeps. Maybe I see him as an escape route, back to the paradise, when things get tough. I don't know and I don't care, all that matters to me is that the thought of him makes me happy. He is the most special thing I own although I don't like calling him a thing, it feels disrespectful which I know is silly. I hope this reminded you of your childhood special toy too and hope u had fun reminiscing., ELLL 3
